The media fraternity is mourning former Nation Media Group journalist Casper Waithaka, who died in a road accident on Friday night. He has been working as the communications officer at the East African Portland Cement Company. Waithaka died when his car rolled several times as he avoided hitting a boda boda rider at the Athi River-Namanga interchange on Mombasa Road. The body was moved to Shalom Community Hospital mortuary. Journalists from various media houses and public relations practitioners eulogised Waithaka as friendly and outgoing.